FT  14 APR 93 / Group 4 to meet prison officials
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALAN PIKE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MANAGERS OF Group 4 Court Services will meet Prison Service officials
tomorrow to discuss the problems which arose during the first week of
Britain's only private prison-escort service.
Four prisoners escaped or were wrongly released last week, when Group 4 took
over the contract for escorting prisoners between prisons and courts in the
east Midlands, Yorkshire and Humberside.
Mr Derek Lewis, chief executive of the Prison Service, will seek an
explanation for the incidents and stress the importance of Group 4 meeting
the quality requirements of its five-year contract.
Group 4 said that it looked forward to tomorrow's meeting. The company was
satisfied that there were adequate explanations for the incidents and said
it was 'entirely happy that the basic principles of the operation are
sound.'
Mr Tony Blair, shadow home secretary, is to raise the issue of private
court-escort services in the Commons.
