<HEADLINE>
FT  14 APR 93 / Andreotti hearings due today
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HAIG SIMONIAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MILAN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BATTLE lines are being drawn in Italy's Senate for today's start of hearings
on lifting the immunity of Mr Giulio Andreotti, seven times Christian
Democrat prime minister, accused of alleged Mafia links, writes Haig
Simonian in Milan.
Mr Andreotti has said he will deliver a 100-page document to a committee of
23 senators, making clear his views on the request by Palermo magistrates to
lift his parliamentary immunity. The magistrates have filed more material
after new testimony from two Mafia informers living in the US. Press leaks
claim this includes details of alleged meetings between Mr Andreotti and
senior Mafia members.
Mr Giovanni Pellegrino, senate committee chairman, said he hoped for a
decision by the end of next week.
