<HEADLINE>
FT  13 APR 93 / Management (The Growing Business): A chance to insure
against debt - In a Nutshell
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Businesses frequently take out credit insurance to cover exports but rarely
use it for their domestic sales, despite the growing risk of UK customers
going bust or delaying payment.
Barclays Bank has launched a short-term credit insurance scheme called
Barclays Sales Protection, intended to cover domestic sales but applicable
also to exports, in the hope of increasing interest.
The new scheme is available to limited companies with annual sales of at
least Pounds 250,000 and a good record of credit management. Premiums
normally cost less than Pounds 1 for every Pounds 100 of cover. The scheme
pays up to 90 per cent of outstanding debts six months after the invoice due
date.
</TEXT>
