<HEADLINE>
FT  13 APR 93 / Observer: Time, gentlemen
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pub customer: 'Gimme a Vinny Jones.'
Barman: 'Sorry, sir, I'm afraid I haven't heard of that one. What is it?'
'Just a quick half and I'm off.'
</TEXT>
