<HEADLINE>
FT  13 APR 93 / Observer: Body count
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It is not just the residents of Los Angeles who have strong feelings about
the case against the four white police officers accused of violating black
man Rodney King's civil rights.
The ugly video film of a man being beaten while he was on the ground has
meant that everyone from Paris to Tokyo has a view on a drama which
threatens to inflame Los Angeles again.
Less well known is the fact that when it comes to racial balance in
recruitment, the record of Los Angeles' police department is above average.
According to a recent University of Nebraska survey of the ethnic mix in 50
US city police forces, New York has the lowest ratio of black police
officers to black residents whilst LA is top.
Some 14 per cent of its officers are black, which is in line with the black
proportion of the city's population.
</TEXT>
