FT  13 APR 93 / Observer: Custom driven
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
International acquisitions are never easy, but Sherwood Group, the
Nottingham lace and lingerie manufacturer, has an unusual problem on its
hands.
It is buying Lepel, number three in the Italian brassiere market, and would
like to sell a few of its chic Latin designs in the UK. But, for some reason
that eludes Observer, Italian women almost always buy B-cup bras. (For the
uninitiated, this is, well, middle-sized.)
British women, explains Sherwood chairman David Parker, come in a much wider
range of sizes. His technical experts are already considering how to adapt
the Bologna production line to cope.
