FT  13 APR 93 / Construction Contracts: Landfill treatment in Wales
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NUTTALL has won the Pounds 8.3m Penarth Haven landfill treatment and phase
one infrastructure works contract for the Cardiff Bay Development
Corporation. The site is located at Penarth Dock, South Glamorgan and
represents the largest single contract awarded by the corporation to date.
The works comprise the containment and encapsulation of approximately
750,000 cu metres of domestic landfill within the old dock. The scheme
includes the application of substantial landfill gas abstraction and
leachate collection systems on the site, together with associated pipework.
Roadworks improvements and associated structures will include the
construction of a new roundabout junction to replace an existing priority
junction between Windsor Road and Penarth Dock Road, as well the provision
of a new roundabout junction at Penarth Dock Road and some 250 metres of
associated carriageways.
